  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd 8 \u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd : \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bbf.\u0b90.\u0b9f\u0bbf.",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Rajitha's 8 ships case: CIT withdraws case",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The CI is withdrawing the case related to the alleged frauds that took place during the operation related to leasing of Mukthuvaram fishing harbor and bringing in 8 fishing vessels to carry out deep sea fishing activities in the name of one who was his liaison secretary when Member of Parliament Rajitha Senaratne was the Fisheries Minister. D. informed the court the day before yesterday (25).",
        "Yesterday, the Criminal Investigation Department announced this when the case file for criminal investigation related to the matter came up for hearing.",
        "The CID announced that it would withdraw the case as the Bribery Corruption Investigation Commission was continuing the case under the charge of corruption.",
        "Earlier, the CIT said that investigations have been started in connection with the complaint filed by the former minister Rajitha Senaratne regarding the landing of 8 vessels and the leasing of the Mukthuvaram fishing harbor during his tenure as the Fisheries Minister. A report was submitted to the Colombo Chief Justice.",
        "State Minister Sanath Nishantha Perera, a resident of Belathalokka Mawatti, Colombo 7, had given a complaint to the CIT, and the CIT had informed the court that the investigations had been started based on it.",
        "The CIT informed the court that these 8 ships were brought to this country in accordance with the agreement made with a Chinese company in the name of Thon Lalith Anuratha Senaviratne, who served as the attachment secretary of former Fisheries Minister Rajitha Senaratne.",
        "It is noteworthy that the CIT had reported to the court that Sri Lanka uses only 50 percent of the capacity given to a country to carry out fishing activities in international waters, and that the agreement was signed to forcefully seize the rights of these fishermen, lease that right to a Chinese company, and receive brokerage money."
      ],
